Class Queue<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • Queue<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of elements held in this collection
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    QueueInterface<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Line

    public class Queue<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements QueueInterface<T>
    A resizable-array implementation of the QueueInterface. The elements in a queue are processed in a FIFO (first-in-first-out) manner. New elements are added to the back of a queue. Elements can only be removed from the front of a queue.
